CITY OF NEW YORK, as Owner of THE D. S. C. DUMPER Q, Appellee, v. THE Tugboat JOSEPH H. MORAN, Moran Towing & Transportation Co., Inc., Appellant. No. 401. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. May 7, 1934. Macklin, Brown, Lenahan & Speer, of New York City (Horace L. Cheyney, of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. Paul Windels, Corp. Counsel, of New York City (P. Pearson Shortridge, of New York City, of counsel), for appellee.

Before L. HAND, SWAN, and CHASE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree affirmed.
